Director, Product Development - Greensboro, NC










☰×North Carolina JobsEmployers / Post JobFind JobsAdvancedArch Capital Group LtdReceive alerts when this company posts new jobs.SubscribeCompany OverviewAll Jobs (28)Director, Product Developmentat Arch Capital Group LtdClick here to Apply Online Share this Job View On MapPosted: 6/6/2017Job Reference #: 1350Categories: Management - Mid-Level (Manager, Director)Job DescriptionJob ID 2017-1350# of Openings 1Job Locations US-NC-GreensboroCategory Product DevelopmentOverview:The Director, Product Development plays a key role in the development and implementation of product strategies for Arch MI with the primary goal of increasing Arch MI profitability. Product strategies include the development of new products, modification of existing products, new distribution channels or the development of complimentary services to the US first lien mortgage insurance product.  The position assist in providing meaningful and timely strategic recommendations based upon market and competitor intelligence to impact executive decisions.   Arch MI is a new and growing mortgage insurance company with a strong and global parent – Arch Capital Group Ltd.  If you’re interested in joining a dynamic company and working with a team of motivated, high caliber people, apply today and come grow with us! Responsibilities:Assist in the development of new products and strategies in concert with customer needs and the Arch MI business model to increase profitability with a secondary success metric of NIW.Build external relationships with key decision makers of customers as well as intermediaries such as trade associations and political organizations.Develop the emerging market strategies through research, proposals, and product solutions. Gain consensus through strong collaboration with other internal departments such as Pricing, Operations, Marketing, Sales, ERM and Legal.Explore gaps or opportunities in competitive capabilities in the market and provide executive management with a roadmap to addressing or capitalizing on them. Provide recommendations with a clear business case which demonstrates bottom-line value.Work continuously with internal customers to ensure that analysis and output are positively impacting decision making and meeting expectations. .Serve as a subject matter expert and resource to internal departments as relates to product positioning and communications.Qualifications:Broad knowledge of residential lending, including: Underwriting, Origination and Secondary Marketing. Broad knowledge of the Mortgage Insurance industry. Excellent market research knowledge to utilize various information sources to gather data. Ability to define problems, establish facts, and draw valid conclusionsHigh degree of creativity with ability to develop ideas outside the status quo.Excellent project management skills.Excellent interpersonal, communication, presentation skills to effectively deliver information to executives and influence decision making.Excellent strategic decision making & problem solving skills with abilities to determine effective resource allocation and address complex customer issues.Analytical skills, including ability to deconstruct, interpret and link together complex competitor activities in order to derive conclusions and recommendations.High level of discretion and organizational awareness. Open and collaborative style; must be comfortable working in an environment where ideas are shared and challenged. Education & Experience: Required knowledge and skills that would typically be acquired through a Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree in business, finance, or economics and 5 to 10 years related experience, including experience in mortgage lending and/or mortgage insurance industry.  About Our CompanyArch Mortgage Insurance Company is the flagship U.S.-based mortgage insurer of Arch Capital Group Ltd., a leading insurance and reinsurance company operating through its subsidiaries worldwide. Based in Greensboro, North Carolina, our company is committed to our employees and our customers.  Our Total Rewards package offers competitive pay and valuable benefits.  Plus you’ll have access to a variety of programs supporting your professional development and a culture that encourages innovation, collaboration and professional growth.CLICK HERE TO APPLY







