  Home  SEC Filings  Arch Capital Group Ltd. (NASDAQ:ACGL) Files An 8-K Other Events     SEC Filings  Arch Capital Group Ltd. (NASDAQ:ACGL) Files An 8-K Other Events  ByME Staff 8-k -July 5, 2017 13  Share on Facebook
Tweet on Twitter


 Arch Capital Group Ltd. (NASDAQ:ACGL) Files An 8-K Other EventsITEM 8.01Other Events.
Arch Capital Group Ltd. issued a press release announcing that on July 1, 2017 it completed its previously announced acquisition of AIG United Guaranty Insurance (Asia Limited) from American International Group, Inc. A copy of the press release is attached to this Current Report on Form 8-K as Exhibit 99.1. 
ITEM 9.01Exhibits.
       EXHIBIT NO.   DESCRIPTION     99.1   Press release dated July 5, 2017 announcing the closing of the acquisition of AIG United Guaranty Insurance (Asia) Limited from American International Group, Inc.   ARCH CAPITAL GROUP LTD. ExhibitEX-99.1 2 ex9917517release.htm EXHIBIT 99.1 RELEASE Exhibit Exhibit 99.1ARCH CAPITAL GROUP LTD. ANNOUNCESCLOSING OF ACQUISITION OF AIG UNITED GUARNATY INSURANCE (ASIA) LIMITED Hamilton,…To view the full exhibit click here About Arch Capital Group Ltd. (NASDAQ:ACGL) Arch Capital Group Ltd. writes insurance and reinsurance on worldwide basis. The Company operates in five segments: insurance, reinsurance, mortgage, other and corporate. The Company’s insurance, reinsurance and mortgage segments are underwriting segments. The insurance segment’s product lines include construction and national accounts; excess and surplus casualty; lenders products; professional lines; programs; property, energy, marine and aviation; travel, accident and health, and other, which includes alternative market risks and excess workers’ compensation. The reinsurance segment’s product lines include casualty; marine and aviation; other specialty; property catastrophe; property excluding property catastrophe, and other, which includes life reinsurance and casualty clash businesses. The mortgage segment includes the results of Arch Mortgage Insurance Company (Arch MI U.S.) and Arch Mortgage Insurance Designated Activity Company (Arch MI Europe).
